pageContext.claim: “You look at our mortality rates, you look at all the things. But they like to compare us to others. So they were talking about New Zealand. New Zealand, it's over, it's over for Zealand. Everything's gone. They're beautiful. They had a massive breakout yesterday.”
pageContext.analysis: Hardly a "massive breakout," more like a minor blip in a country widely hailed for its effective response to the coronavirus. In terms of total cases, New Zealand ranks 160th in the world. In terms of deaths, it ranks 161st. In terms of cases or deaths per million people, it ranks 174th.
